items.title: Path tracing - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Path tracing - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Path tracing is a computer graphics Monte Carlo method of rendering images of 
three-dimensional scenes such that the global illumination is faithful to reality.
